import React, {Component} from 'react' import 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.css'; class DisplayError extends Component{ constructor(props){ //any data passed to a class object is stored inside props , to receive it i need props in the constructor and super parameters super(props) this.state={ first: this.props.first.first.first[0] } console.log(this.props) console.log(this.state.first) } render(){ const error_code = this.state.first.error_code const error_type = this.state.first.error_type const error_description = this.state.first.error_description const robot_tags = this.state.first.robot_tags console.log(error_code + " DisplayError commponent") return (



{error_code}
{error_type}
{error_description}
{robot_tags}

) } } export default DisplayError
